jk","Raby, Durham, England":"Raby, Durham, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Staindrop, Durham, England":"Staindrop, Durham, England","Raby Castle, Durham, England":"Raby Castle, Durham, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1130–1172":"1130–1172","1132–Male":"1132–Deceased","1134–Male":"1134–Deceased","1140–1197":"1140–1197","1149–Female":"1149–Deceased","1170–1248":"1170–1248","1110–1140":"1110–1140","1104–1200":"1104–1200","about 1140":"about 1140","about 1170":"about 1170","1110":"1110","1132":"1132","1197":"1197","1130":"1130","1140":"1140","1172":"1172","1170":"1170","1248":"1248","1149":"1149","1104":"1104","1200":"1200","1134":"1134","18 May 1170":"18 May 1170","Durham, England":"Durham, England, United Kingdom","Raby, Durham, England":"Raby, Durham, England, United Kingdom","Staindrop, Durham, England":"Staindrop, Durham, England","Raby Castle, Durham, England":"Raby Castle, Durham, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Maldred","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old English female personal name <i>Mildþrӯð</i>, derived from <i>mild</i> ‘gentle’ + <i>þrӯð</i> ‘strength’. This was the name of a 7th-century abbess, who had a less famous but equally saintly elder sister called <i>Mildburh</i> and a younger sister called <i>Mildgӯð</i>; all were daughters of a certain  Queen Ermenburh . Their names illustrate clearly the Old English pattern of combining and recombining the same small group of name elements within a single family. This name was in fairly regular localized use until the early 18th century and it enjoyed a strong revival throughout England in the 19th century. Its use declined from the 1930s onwards."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Maldred FitzDolphin Lord of Raby was born in 1130, in Raby Castle, Durham, England, United Kingdom, his father, Dolfin fitzUchtred, was 20 and his mother, Adelicia FitzWalcher, was 27. He married Joan de Stuteville about 1170, in Raby, Durham, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1172, in Staindrop, Durham, England, at the age of 42, and was buried in Durham, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1130–1172":"1130–1172","1132–Male":"1132–Surnud","1134–Male":"1134–Surnud","1140–1197":"1140–1197","1149–Female":"1149–Surnud","1170–1248":"1170–1248","1110–1140":"1110–1140","1104–1200":"1104–1200","about 1140":"umbes 1140","about 1170":"umbes 1170","1110":"1110","1132":"1132","1197":"1197","1130":"1130","1140":"1140","1172":"1172","1170":"1170","1248":"1248","1149":"1149","1104":"1104","1200":"1200","1134":"1134","18 May 1170":"18. mai 1170","Durham, England":"Durham, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Raby, Durham, England":"Raby, Durham, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Staindrop, Durham, England":"Staindrop, Durham, England","Raby Castle, Durham, England":"Raby Castle, Durham, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1130–1172":"1130–1172","1132–Male":"1132–Kuollut","1134–Male":"1134–Kuollut","1140–1197":"1140–1197","1149–Female":"1149–Kuollut","1170–1248":"1170–1248","1110–1140":"1110–1140","1104–1200":"1104–1200","about 1140":"noin 1140","about 1170":"noin 1170","1110":"1110","1132":"1132","1197":"1197","1130":"1130","1140":"1140","1172":"1172","1170":"1170","1248":"1248","1149":"1149","1104":"1104","1200":"1200","1134":"1134","18 May 1170":"18. toukokuuta 1170","Durham, England":"Durham, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Raby, Durham, England":"Raby, Durham, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Staindrop, Durham, England":"Staindrop, Durham, England","Raby Castle, Durham, England":"Raby Castle, Durham, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1130–1172":"1130–1172","1132–Male":"1132–Décédé","1134–Male":"1134–Décédé","1140–1197":"1140–1197","1149–Female":"1149–Décédée","1170–1248":"1170–1248","1110–1140":"1110–1140","1104–1200":"1104–1200","about 1140":"environ 1140","about 1170":"environ 1170","1110":"1110","1132":"1132","1197":"1197","1130":"1130","1140":"1140",